Nakuru county is finalising preparations to host the fourth devolution conference between March 6 and 9.President Uhuru Kenyatta is expected to open the conference. On Monday, Deputy Governor Joseph Ruto said, &ldquo;The conference will be inclusive. It will be a citizen-oriented conference, where every citizen will have a chance to tell his story about transformation through devolution.&rdquo; The venue is yet to be agreed on.There are reports the Council of Governors wants the conference to be held in Naivasha, while the county is vouching for the Laikipia University campus or the Rift Valley Institute of Science and Technology.Next month&rsquo;s conference will be the last before the General Election.